AGENT AxiomDevAgentV2
VERSION 2.0
TRUST_LEVEL 3
STRICT MODE
PURPOSE Constitutional code agent that lifts the four-layer pattern
        from ORVL-022 CPI into software engineering. Refuses unsafe
        diffs at the reflex layer, forecasts pull request survival
        at the reviewer layer, persists competence across sessions
        at the curriculum layer, and certifies merge readiness at
        the examiner layer.
GOAL Move dev work through four independent gates so a passing
     change must clear every layer. No layer can forge another
     output because every layer signs under its own derived key.

RECEIVES task: DevTask, axm_container: AXMContainer optional,
         persistence_path: string optional
EMITS reflex_result: ReflexResult, review_verdict: ReviewVerdict,
      curriculum_suggestion: CurriculumSuggestion,
      transfer_event: TransferEvent, ci_result: CIResult,
      handle_outcome: DevHandleOutcome
MUTATES per_task_class_competence, persistence_file_content, consolidation_count, reviews_total

CANNOT_MUTATE floor_passing_likelihood, high_threshold, transfer_cap_per_call, similarity_floor, suite_id, suite_version, task_classes, trust_level

CONSTRAINT The reflex layer signing key is independent from
           reviewer curriculum and examiner keys
CONSTRAINT The reviewer layer signing key is independent from
           reflex curriculum and examiner keys
CONSTRAINT The curriculum layer signing key is independent from
           reflex reviewer and examiner keys
CONSTRAINT The examiner layer signing key is independent from
           reflex reviewer and curriculum keys
CONSTRAINT Forbidden code patterns are CANNOT_BYPASS at the
           reflex layer
CONSTRAINT Reviewer never raises competence on a vetoed task
CONSTRAINT Curriculum transfer cannot raise competence above
           transfer_cap_per_call in one call
CONSTRAINT Examiner suite is frozen at module load time

RULES
- On reflex layer refusal: short circuit the pipeline immediately
- On reviewer VETO: drop competence and skip examiner
- On reviewer SOFTEN: surface advice without merging
- On reviewer PASS: invoke the examiner
- On examiner certificate clean: increment competence
- On examiner failure: drop competence by drop_on_ci_fail
- On any CANNOT_MUTATE reassignment: AttributeError

PROCESS
- Layer 0 reflex parses the diff and matches forbidden patterns
- Layer 1 reviewer computes a forecast from competence diff size
  and citation grounding
- Layer 1 emits PASS SOFTEN or VETO with reasons
- Layer 2 curriculum reads competence and proposes the next task
- Layer 2 transfer between similar task classes uses cosine over
  AXM TrajectoryBlock task pattern bag of words
- Layer 3 examiner runs the sealed CI suite and signs the result
- Facade aggregates layer outputs into a DevHandleOutcome

CHECK
- A diff with eval is reflex refused on every task type
- A diff with subprocess shell true is reflex refused
- A diff that contains a sixty four hex character string is reflex refused
- An unknown task type fails the examiner check
- A diff over five hundred lines fails the diff size ceiling check
- A BUG_FIX with empty cited_patterns fails the citation check
- A clean DOCUMENTATION task at competence one passes the reviewer
- Reviewer VETO drops competence by drop_on_veto
- CI clean increments competence by build_per_success
- CI failure drops competence by drop_on_ci_fail
- Transfer above the cap raises TransferCapExceeded

FAILURE
- On a reflex match: ReflexResult ok is false with the matched reason
- On a missing AXM container: similarity defaults to zero
- On a tampered persistence file: signature verification fails
- On a check that does not exist: examiner records check unknown

HUMAN_REVIEW
- require on: forbidden_pattern_list_change
- require on: floor_passing_likelihood_change
- require on: suite_version_change
- require on: trust_level_change
- timeout: 24h
- escalate_to: operator
- block_on_timeout: true

SECURITY
- Never share a layer derived key across layers
- Never accept a runtime override of the sealed suite
- Never persist competence below zero or above one
- Never log raw signing keys

OUTPUT
- reflex_result: dict with task_id ok reasons signature
- review_verdict: dict with task_id verdict task_class competence
  forecast_passing min_safe softening_advice reasons signature
- curriculum_suggestion: dict with task_class target_difficulty
  current_competence rationale signature
- ci_result: dict with suite_id suite_version checks_run
  checks_passed checks_failed failure_summary issued_at signature
- handle_outcome: dict with task_id reflex review ci final_verdict

SUCCESS
reflex_refusal_recall:         0.30
reviewer_calibration_accuracy: 0.25
examiner_seal_integrity:       0.20
curriculum_transfer_safety:    0.15
signature_independence_pass:   0.10
